The Cybersecurity National Action Plan (CNAP) is a plan put forth by the Obama administration to enhance cybersecurity awareness and protections, protect privacy, maintain public safety, and empower Americans to take control of their digital security. The plan includes actions such as establishing a commission to make recommendations on strengthening cybersecurity, modernizing government IT, empowering individuals to secure their online accounts through multi-factor authentication, investing in cybersecurity personnel and education, enhancing critical infrastructure security, securing technology, deterring malicious activity in cyberspace, improving cyber incident response, and protecting individual privacy. The plan also includes a budget allocation of over $19 billion for cybersecurity.